        <h2>Dr. Lavian Expertise and Experience</h2>

        <p>Dr. Lavian is a network communications expert with a Ph.D. in computer science from the University of California, Berkeley, specializing in network communications. His research focused on network communications, telecommunication systems, mobile wireless, and Internet protocols. He has extensive experience in software development, network protocols, and network communications technology products. His expertise includes wireless and wireline systems, routers, switches, and network devices. He has served as a scientist at UC Berkeley's RAD Lab and as a Technical Co-Chair for IEEE Interconnects at Stanford University.</p>

        <p>With support from UC Berkeley's SkyDeck startup accelerator in recent years, Dr. Lavian has led a development team in innovating communications search engine architecture that converts interactive voice response (IVR) into a Google-like cloud-based search experience. Above all, this solution addresses the significant challenge of navigating the IVR menus of large call centers effectively and efficiently.</p>

        <h3>Academic Endeavors</h3>

        <p>Dr. Lavian has been an active contributor to the academic community. He has published numerous papers in prestigious journals and conferences, reflecting his deep understanding and research in network communications, telecommunications, and related fields. His publications span topics such as network security, multimedia streaming, voice over IP (VoIP), and cloud computing, demonstrating the breadth and depth of his expertise. Additionally, Dr. Lavian has been a prolific inventor, with numerous patents in network communications, telecommunications, and related fields.</p>

        <h3>Industry Experience</h3>

        <p>Dr. Lavian has an impressive industry experience track record, having held critical roles in various technology and telecommunications companies. He worked as a scientist and researcher at UC Berkeley, contributing to advancing network communications technology. His industry roles have involved developing and managing hardware and software products, leading research and development teams, and contributing to technological innovation.</p>

        <p>Nortel Networks, now defunct but once one of the largest networking companies globally, was a prominent player in developing technology for telephone and Internet networks and contributed to many critical communications standards. Over the years, its products were used by major businesses, governments, and internet service providers worldwide, making it one of the key companies in the history of telecommunications and networking.</p>

        <p>During his over ten years at Nortel Networks' Research Labs, Dr. Lavian was a trailblazer in the telecommunications field. He led the development of the first network resource-scheduling service for Grid computing and was the first to demonstrate the dynamic transatlantic allocation of 10Gbs Lambdas as a grid service. His creation of the first wire-speed active network device on commercial hardware is a testament to his innovative spirit. His senior membership in IEEE and active participation in ACM and IEEE-CNSV further underscore his pioneering work.</p>

        <p>He has also served as Principal Investigator for projects at the Defense Advanced Research Projects Agency (DARPA) of the U.S. Department of Defense, including a research project for the U.S. Air Force Research Lab (AFRL) involving routing and switching optical SONET and DWDM high-speed networks.</p>

        <p>Above all, Dr. Lavian, an expert with decades of experience, provides expert consulting services and expert witness testimony in patent and commercial litigation cases for law firms. His expertise in network communications, telecommunications, and Internet protocols, combined with his extensive industry and academic experience, make him a valuable resource for clients seeking expert consulting in these fields.</p>

        <h3>Publications &amp; Patents</h3>

        <p>Dr. Lavian has a diverse publication record in networking and telecommunications, with key contributions in areas such as network scheduling, software-defined networking, and IVR systems enhancement. His work also covers topics like network security, multimedia communication, and cloud computing. Many of his publications have been collaborations with esteemed researchers and have been presented at prestigious conferences. Furthermore, Dr. Lavian holds multiple US and international patents spanning network resource scheduling, active network technologies, IVR enhancements, and various other innovative telecommunications solutions.</p>

        <h3>Expert Consulting &amp; Testimony</h3>

        <p>Dr. Lavian offers consulting and expert witness services in patent infringement, trade secrets, and commercial disputes related to networking, telecommunications, and internet technologies, including over the Internet. He has been engaged as an expert consultant in complex telecommunications litigation matters, leveraging his deep knowledge of network architectures, protocols, and technologies. His experience consulting and providing testimony spans a broad range of technology disputes involving data communications, VoIP, network security, and wireless technologies.</p>

